        <updateDate>2020-03-18T13:32:07Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>IoT Standards Leadership Act of 2019</strong></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Commerce to report to Congress a study of (1) international bodies that set technological standards relevant to internet-connected devices, and (2) the appropriate means to ensure robust U.S. leadership in such bodies. (Technological standards for emerging technologies, such as next-generation wireless data communications, are typically set by international bodies that comprise various stakeholders, such as equipment manufacturers in the relevant industries.) </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
